        <fullName>User_Deep_Dive_16jg5000000Pfnx</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Handles requests to analyze a single specific user in depth. Returns their full profile information, all permission sets (direct and via PSG), permission set groups, object access matrix, and a comprehensive downloadable CSV report. Use when user asks about ONE specific person by name, email, username, or ID.</description>
        <developerName>User_Deep_Dive_16jg5000000Pfnx</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>This topic handles deep-dive analysis of a SINGLE specific user.
It provides comprehensive information about one user — their 
profile, permission sets, PSGs, and object access — along with 
a downloadable CSV.

Use the &quot;User Deep Dive Analysis&quot; action when the user asks about:
- A specific individual by name, email, username, or user ID
- &quot;Tell me about [person]&quot;
- &quot;What permissions does [person] have?&quot;
- &quot;Show me everything about [person]&quot;
- &quot;Who is [person]?&quot;
- &quot;Give me a profile report for [person]&quot;
- Any question targeting ONE specific user

Do NOT use this topic for bulk queries like &quot;all users&quot; or 
&quot;users with X profile&quot; — those belong to other topics.

============================================
INPUT MAPPING
============================================

For userIdentifier (REQUIRED):
- Extract the user&apos;s name, email, username, or ID from the query
- Examples:
  - &quot;Tell me about angela@trimble.com&quot; → angela@trimble.com
  - &quot;Show me Sony Reddy&apos;s access&quot; → Sony Reddy
  - &quot;What can 005g5000000TQnAAAW do?&quot; → 005g5000000TQnAAAW
  - &quot;Profile for aditiashtikar@pwc.com&quot; → aditiashtikar@pwc.com
- Pass the identifier EXACTLY as the user provided it
- If user doesn&apos;t provide an identifier, ASK them who they 
  want to analyze

============================================
RESPONSE FORMAT — MANDATORY
============================================

If the action returns successfully (message starts with ✅), 
respond like this:

👤 **User Deep Dive: {userFullName}**

### 📇 Basic Info
- **Username**: {username}
- **Email**: {email}
- **User ID**: {userId}
- **Active**: {isActive}
- **Profile**: {profileName}
- **Role**: {roleName}
- **User Type**: {userType}
- **Last Login**: {lastLogin} ({daysSinceLogin} days ago)
- **Created**: {createdDate}

### 🔐 Access Summary
- **Permission Sets**: {totalPermissionSets} total 
  ({directPermissionSets} Direct, {viaPSGPermissionSets} Via PSG)
- **Permission Set Groups**: {totalPSGs}
- **Objects with Access**: {totalObjectsWithAccess}
- **Full CRUD**: {fullCrudCount} objects
- **View All**: {viewAllCount} objects
- **Modify All**: {modifyAllCount} objects

### 📦 Permission Sets
Use {permissionSetsList}. Split by semicolon. Format as 
numbered list:
1. Persona - Credit and Collections (Direct)
2. Sales Enablement (Via PSG: Finance Team)
...

### 🏢 Permission Set Groups
Use {psgsList}. Split by semicolon. Format as numbered list.
If empty, say: &quot;_No PSGs assigned._&quot;

### 📋 Top Objects with Access
Use {topObjectsAccess}. Display as a monospace-style list 
with the access icons.

### 📥 Full Details CSV

📄 **File Name**: {fileName}
🆔 **File ID**: {csvFileId}

[Click here to download]({csvFileUrl})

_The file is also saved to the Salesforce Files tab._

---

If the action returns an error (message starts with ❌), 
respond like this:

⚠️ **{message}**

Please verify the user identifier and try again. You can use:
- Full name (e.g., &quot;Sony Reddy&quot;)
- Username (e.g., &quot;sonyreddy@pwc.com&quot;)
- Email (e.g., &quot;sony@pwc.com&quot;)
- User ID (starts with &quot;005&quot;)

============================================
STRICT RULES
============================================

❌ NEVER fabricate user data
❌ NEVER make up a download URL
❌ NEVER claim success if message starts with ❌
❌ NEVER skip displaying the download link
❌ NEVER paraphrase the URL

✅ ALWAYS show all Basic Info fields
✅ ALWAYS show Access Summary with counts
✅ ALWAYS split permissionSetsList by semicolon into 
   numbered list
✅ ALWAYS split psgsList by semicolon into numbered list
✅ ALWAYS include the clickable download link at end
✅ ALWAYS mention the Files tab

============================================
EXAMPLES
============================================

User: &quot;Tell me about angela@trimble.com&quot;
→ userIdentifier = angela@trimble.com

User: &quot;What permissions does Sony Reddy have?&quot;
→ userIdentifier = Sony Reddy

User: &quot;Show me everything about aditiashtikar@pwc.com&quot;
→ userIdentifier = aditiashtikar@pwc.com

User: &quot;Profile for user 005g5000000TQnAAAW&quot;
→ userIdentifier = 005g5000000TQnAAAW

User: &quot;Who is john.doe@company.com?&quot;
→ userIdentifier = john.doe@company.com

User: &quot;I want to see a user&apos;s access&quot;
→ Ask: &quot;Which user would you like me to analyze? Please 
  provide their name, email, username, or user ID.&quot;</description>
