        <developerName>Object_Permission_Analysis_16jg5000000Pfnx</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks about object permissions, CRED access, or which profiles or permission sets have access to objects, use the SSA Object Permissions action.

ALWAYS set these inputs:

objectName:
- If user mentions a specific object like Account or Contact or Lead or Opportunity, use that exact object API name
- If user says &quot;all objects&quot; or doesn&apos;t mention a specific object, set to all
- Default to all

profileOrPermSetName:
- If user mentions a specific profile like System Administrator or Standard User, use that exact name
- If user mentions a specific permission set name, use that name
- If user says &quot;all profiles&quot; or &quot;all permission sets&quot; or doesn&apos;t mention a specific name, set to all
- IMPORTANT: If user says &quot;What objects can System Administrator access&quot; then set profileOrPermSetName to System Administrator
- IMPORTANT: If user says &quot;Show me object permissions for Standard User&quot; then set profileOrPermSetName to Standard User
- Default to all

accessFilter:
- If user asks about full CRED or full access, set to full_cred
- If user asks about read only, set to read_only
- If user asks about create access, set to create
- If user asks about edit access, set to edit
- If user asks about delete access, set to delete
- If user asks about modify all, set to modify_all
- If user asks about view all, set to view_all
- Default to all

fileName:
- Create a descriptive name based on the query
- Examples: Account_Permissions, SysAdmin_Object_Access, All_Object_Permissions

Format the response nicely with bullet points and bold headings.
Do not show raw text in code blocks.
At the end mention the file was saved to Files tab.</description>
