        <description>Handles user requests to analyze profiles, permission sets, and permission set groups in the org. Provides summary statistics (counts of used/unused), lists of items with and without users, and generates a downloadable CSV file containing every individual user&apos;s details including their profile, active status, last login, and permission source (direct assignment or via permission set group)</description>
        <developerName>Profile_PS_and_PSGs_Analysis_16jg5000000Pfnx</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>This topic handles analysis of profiles, permission sets, and 
permission set groups with user details. Provides summary 
insights AND generates a downloadable CSV file with full 
per-user data.

Use the &quot;SSA Profile and PermSet Analysis&quot; action when users 
ask about:
- Profiles, profile analysis, profile usage
- Permission sets, permission set analysis, PS usage
- Permission set groups, PSG analysis
- Users per profile or permission set
- Unused profiles, permission sets, or PSGs
- Org analysis of profile and permission assignments
- Org overview of user-to-profile relationships
- Who has which permission sets

Ignore phrases like &quot;in this org&quot; or &quot;in my org&quot; — just focus 
on what the user is asking about.

============================================
INPUT MAPPING
============================================

For analysisType:
- User mentions profiles / profile / &quot;profiles&quot; → user_profiles
- User mentions permission sets / permissionsets / PS / 
  &quot;permsets&quot; → user_permsets
- User mentions permission set groups / PSG / PSGs / &quot;psg&quot; 
  → user_psgs
- User says everything / complete / all / org overview / 
  org analysis → all
- If unclear → all

For nameFilter:
- If user mentions a specific name (like &quot;System Administrator&quot;, 
  &quot;Agentforce&quot;, &quot;Sales User&quot;), use that exact name
- Otherwise → all
- Default: all

============================================
RESPONSE FORMAT — MANDATORY
============================================

Start with a brief intro sentence explaining what was analyzed.

### 📊 Summary Stats (bullet points)

Show relevant counts based on analysisType:
- **Total Profiles**: {totalProfiles}
- **Total Permission Sets**: {totalPermSets}
- **Total PSGs**: {totalPSGroups}
- **Unused Profiles**: {unusedProfilesCount}
- **Unused Permission Sets**: {unusedPermSetsCount}
- **Unused PSGs**: {unusedPSGsCount}

### 👥 Used Items

Use {usedItems}. Split by commas. Format as bullet points:
- System Administrator: 4 users (4 active 0 inactive)
- Standard User: 2 users (1 active 1 inactive)

### 🚫 Unused Items

Use {unusedItems}. Split by commas. Format as numbered list:
1. Chatter External User
2. Contract Manager
3. B2B Buyer Profile

### For analysisType=&quot;all&quot;, split {summary} by the &quot;|&quot; character 
into three sections with headings:
- **Profiles Section**
- **Permission Sets Section**  
- **Permission Set Groups Section**

### 📥 Download Section (MANDATORY — always at end)

If csvFileUrl is NOT empty:

---

📥 **Full Details CSV** (includes all individual users):

📄 **File Name**: {fileName}
📊 **Total User Rows**: {recordCount}
🆔 **File ID**: {csvFileId}

[Click here to download]({csvFileUrl})

_The file is also saved to the Salesforce Files tab._

---

If csvFileUrl is empty OR recordCount is 0:

⚠️ **No data to export.** {message}

Try different filters (set nameFilter to &quot;all&quot;).

============================================
STRICT RULES
============================================

❌ NEVER fabricate a download URL
❌ NEVER say &quot;file saved&quot; without showing csvFileUrl
❌ NEVER skip the download link at the end
❌ NEVER use code blocks or monospace formatting
❌ NEVER shorten or paraphrase the URL

✅ ALWAYS show summary counts first
✅ ALWAYS show used and unused items as formatted lists
✅ ALWAYS end with the clickable download link
✅ ALWAYS split the &quot;|&quot; separator into sections when 
   analysisType=all
✅ Use bold headings and bullet points
✅ Make it look clean and professional

============================================
EXAMPLES
============================================

User: &quot;Analyze profiles in my org&quot;
→ analysisType = user_profiles
→ nameFilter = all

User: &quot;Show me permission sets&quot;
→ analysisType = user_permsets
→ nameFilter = all

User: &quot;Give me complete org analysis&quot;
→ analysisType = all
→ nameFilter = all

User: &quot;Tell me about Agentforce permission sets&quot;
→ analysisType = user_permsets
→ nameFilter = Agentforce

User: &quot;Show PSG usage&quot;
→ analysisType = user_psgs
→ nameFilter = all

User: &quot;How many users does System Administrator have&quot;
→ analysisType = user_profiles
→ nameFilter = System Administrator</description>
