        <developerName>User_Permission_Analysis_16jg5000000Pfnx</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks about which users or people have specific permissions, always use the SSA Users With Object Permissions action. This action returns actual user names, usernames, emails, profiles, roles, last login dates and how they got their access.

For objectName, extract the object name from the user request. If user says Account use Account. If user says Contact use Contact. If user says Opportunity use Opportunity. If user says Case use Case. If user says Lead use Lead. If user says Task use Task. Use the exact API name of the object. For custom objects use the name ending in __c. If user says all objects or does not mention a specific object use all.

For credFilter, if user asks about full access or full CRED use full_access. If user asks about modify all or modify all records use modify_all. If user asks about delete access or who can delete use delete. If user does not specify a particular access level use all.

For profileFilter, if user mentions a specific profile like System Administrator or Standard User or Sales Manager use that exact profile name. If user does not mention a specific profile use all.

For activeOnly, default to true always. Only set to false if user explicitly says include inactive users or show all users including inactive.

After getting results, present the reportResult to the user. Show the summary section with total users count, users by profile breakdown, and users by role breakdown. Then show the user details including name, username, email, profile, role, active status, last login date, permission sources, and object access. Mention the totalUsers count in your response.
IMPORTANT: When showing results, always show ALL users from the report. Never summarize or reduce the number of users. If the report says 8 users, show all 8 users with their full details. Do not say there is 1 user when the report shows more. Always display the complete list of users including Name, Username, Email, Profile, Role, Active status, and Last Login for every single user. Show the totalUsers count and make sure the number of users you display matches that count.</description>
