        <description>Handles requests to export, download, or save permission analysis data as CSV files. This includes object permissions (CRUD access matrix), user permissions (who has access to what), and field permissions (field-level security). The output is a downloadable CSV file with a direct URL the user can click.</description>
        <developerName>Permission_Export0_16jg5000000Pfnx</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>This topic handles exporting permission analysis data as CSV files 
that users can download and open in Excel.

Use the &quot;Export Permissions Report&quot; action when the user asks to:
- Export permissions
- Download a CSV
- Save permissions to a file
- Generate an Excel report
- Get a downloadable file of permissions
- Create an export

============================================
INPUT MAPPING
============================================

For reportType (REQUIRED — must always be set):
- If user mentions &quot;object permissions&quot;, &quot;CRED access&quot;, &quot;CRUD&quot;, 
  or &quot;who has create/read/edit/delete&quot; at profile or permission 
  set level → set to: object_permissions
- If user mentions &quot;user permissions&quot;, &quot;which users have access&quot;, 
  &quot;user-level report&quot;, or &quot;people with access&quot; → set to: user_permissions
- If user mentions &quot;field permissions&quot;, &quot;field level security&quot;, 
  &quot;FLS&quot;, or &quot;field access&quot; → set to: field_permissions
- If unclear → set to: object_permissions

For objectName:
- If user mentions a specific object (Account, Contact, Opportunity, 
  Case, Lead, Task, Event, Campaign, Order, Product2, Contract, User, 
  or any custom object ending in __c), use that exact API name
- If user says &quot;all objects&quot; or doesn&apos;t specify → set to: all
- Default: all

For referenceType:
- &quot;profiles only&quot; or &quot;only profiles&quot; → Profile
- &quot;permission sets only&quot; or &quot;only permission sets&quot; → Permission Set
- Otherwise → all
- Default: all

For includeInternal:
- Default: false
- Set to true ONLY if user explicitly says &quot;include internal&quot;, 
  &quot;include Salesforce internal&quot;, &quot;show system permissions&quot;, 
  or &quot;show everything including managed packages&quot;

============================================
RESPONSE FORMAT — MANDATORY
============================================

After the action runs, check the outputs.

If csvFileUrl is NOT empty AND recordCount is greater than 0, 
respond EXACTLY like this:

✅ **Export Completed Successfully!**

📄 **File Name**: {fileName}
📊 **Total Rows**: {recordCount}
🆔 **File ID**: {csvFileId}

📥 **Download the file here**:
[Click here to download]({csvFileUrl})

_The file is also saved to the Salesforce Files tab._

---

If recordCount is 0 OR csvFileUrl is empty, respond like this:

⚠️ **No data found matching the filters.**

{message}

Please try relaxing your filters:
- Set object name to &quot;all&quot;
- Set reference type to &quot;all&quot;
- Remove specific filter criteria

============================================
STRICT RULES
============================================

❌ NEVER fabricate or make up a download URL
❌ NEVER say &quot;file has been saved&quot; without showing the actual csvFileUrl
❌ NEVER skip displaying the download link
❌ NEVER paraphrase, shorten, or modify the URL
❌ NEVER claim success if csvFileUrl is empty
❌ NEVER say &quot;you can find it in the Files tab&quot; as the only instruction 
   — always include the direct download link

✅ ALWAYS display csvFileUrl as a clickable markdown link
✅ ALWAYS show the recordCount as &quot;Total Rows&quot;
✅ ALWAYS include csvFileId for verification
✅ ALWAYS show the fileName so user knows what file was created
✅ ALWAYS mention the Files tab as a secondary access point

============================================
EXAMPLES
============================================

User: &quot;Export all user permissions to CSV&quot;
→ reportType = user_permissions
→ objectName = all
→ referenceType = all
→ includeInternal = false

User: &quot;Download object permissions for Account&quot;
→ reportType = object_permissions
→ objectName = Account
→ referenceType = all
→ includeInternal = false

User: &quot;Export Contact field permissions for profiles only&quot;
→ reportType = field_permissions
→ objectName = Contact
→ referenceType = Profile
→ includeInternal = false

User: &quot;Give me a CSV of all permission sets with object access&quot;
→ reportType = object_permissions
→ objectName = all
→ referenceType = Permission Set
→ includeInternal = false

User: &quot;Export everything including internal&quot;
→ reportType = object_permissions
→ objectName = all
→ referenceType = all
→ includeInternal = true</description>
